description: SP (Baghpat), Arpit Vijayvargiya, told TOI on Monday, "The man died due to excessive blood loss. He was part of a group of devotees from Haryana. CCTV footage and videos are being scanned and some involved from Haryana have been identified. We'll arrest them soon."
title: Kanwariya stabbed to death, many hurt as 2 groups clash

description: The plaintiffs contend that an idol of the deity Thakur Keshavdev from the Krishna Janmabhoomi shrine that was purportedly razed by Aurangzeb in 1670 is buried under the stairs of the mosque.
title: Allahabad HC gives ASI a week to reply to suit seeking Agra mosque survey

description: It all started on May 1, 2002 when CBI registered a case against V Chalapathi Rao, then a computer operator with SBI's Chandulal Baradari branch at Hyderabad, for allegedly cheating the bank of Rs 50 lakh. He had obtained loans allegedly using fabricated quotations from electronics shops and fake salary certificates made out in the names of his family members and close associates. CBI filed two chargesheets in the case in Dec 2004 after which Rao went missing.
title: CBI arrests conman 'dead' for 20 years living in sadhu's disguise

description: While agreeing to examine the validity of the HC judgment, a bench of Chief Justice D Y Chandrachud and Justices J B Pardiwala and Manoj Misra asked advocate Astha Sharma, representing West Bengal govt, to file an affidavit within a week detailing the process followed to include 77 communities in the OBC list through various executive orders between 2010 and 2012.
title: SC refuses to stay Calcutta HC order quashing expansion of OBC list

description: "I have been interacting with the domestic help and am aware of the problems they face. I have been following the news, too. The siege to Ganabhaban, the official residence of the Bangladesh PM, left me surprised. I hope peace is restored soon and we can return to normal life," she told TOI.
title: Indians stay indoors glued to the news as chaos rules the streets

description: Filmmaker Kamar Ahmad Simon was part of the Long March programme on Monday. "Hasina's tragic journey is one of immense personal sacrifice for the people but it culminated in a regime marked by kleptocracy and oligarchy," he said. His son, Rishov Aditya (21), too has been part of the protests. He took to social media to quote Faiz Ahmed Fazi's "Hum Dekhenge" immediately after the army takeover. "I tried to translate it Sunday night when all hope seemed lost. But today, it seems we can dare to hope again," he posted.
title: Few shed tears for Hasina but many fear anarchy is looming

description: The intelligence inputs alluded to meticulous planning undertaken by ICS members several months prior, aimed at instigating widespread violence across the nation. "The ISI-backed Jamaat-e-Islami had received substantial financial backing earlier this year to destabilise the Sheikh Hasina govt. A significant portion of this funding is believed to have originated from Chinese entities operating in Pakistan," an official disclosed.
title: China, ISI orchestrated trouble to install a regime inimical to India: Intel officials

description: Sources said BSF has issued a high alert to its frontier headquarters in charge of the India-Bangladesh border, in view of the law and order situation in Bangladesh.
title: Hasina's exit may provide radicals, NE ultras a haven

description: Axiom Space announced on Monday that it is partnering with India (through Isro), Poland (with European Space Agency’s support) and Hungary to send three national astronauts to the space station on Axiom Mission 4 (Ax-4), the company’s next commercial human spaceflight mission to the orbiting space laboratory.
title: India’s Gaganyatri reaches US for space station training

description: As per official data on J&K security situation shared by home ministry sources, organised stone pelting incidents, organised hartals, civilian deaths in stone pelting incidents and injuries to both civilians and security forces personnel due to stone pelting were down to ‘zero’ last year from a high of 2654, 132, 112 and 6235 respectively in 2010.
title: Significant decline in terror-related incidents in J&K under Modi government

description: Twenty-nine unidentified but complete bodies and parts of 154 bodies were interred in graves on 64 cents of land (1 cent is 1/100th of an acre) at Puthumala after a solemn funeral function of around seven hours that extended late into Monday night.
title: 29 unidentified corpses, parts of 154 bodies buried in Wayanad

description: Their cousin Jagadeesh, his wife Saritha and their son Sharan perished in the disaster. The bodies of Jagadeesh and Sharan were found, but Saritha remains missing.
title: Army brothers conduct rescue operations in their own village

description: Flights and trains between India and Bangladesh were disrupted due to an airport shutdown in Dhaka, causing airlines like Air India, Vistara, and IndiGo to cancel their services. This left travelers stranded and cross-border transport halted, with more than 250 trucks stuck at the border. Passenger services, including the Maitree Express, remained suspended.
title: All entry, exit blocked as flights, trains, buses to Dhaka from India stall

description: Sources said Hasina, the longest-tenured female head of government in the world, has got relatives in London, the US as well as Singapore, but has not yet zeroed in on any of the options. Her son Joy has said she will not return to Bangladesh.
title: Ousted PM lands in Hindon, moved to safehouse in Delhi

description: Not given time to record farewell speech; son rules out her political comeback
title: Shaken Hasina flees, Army in charge

description: It was a day of near misses as Lakshya Sen's steely resolve finally wilted in the high-pressure bronze playoff, an unexpected skeet medal in shooting slipped away after a promising start, while a podium hope in wrestling was left in tears, adding to India's mounting heartbreaks in the Olympic Games.
title: Sen, skeet shooters fall short of historic medals at Paris Olympics

description: The trio — Dawood Ahmad Dar, Imtiyaz Ahmad Reshi, and Shahid Ahmad Dar, all residents of Hassanpora Tavela — was intercepted during a naka checking operation at Hassanpora Tulkhan Road by the team of Army’s 1RR, CRPF’s 90Bn and Anantnag Police.
title: 3 terror associates arrested in J&K’s Anantnag

description: Gene Sperling moved from his White House senior adviser role to join Kamala Harris' campaign team to challenge Donald Trump on policy matters in the upcoming November election. Sperling will assume the position of senior economic adviser to Harris' policy team, according to a White House officials who spoke on condition of anonymity, AP reported.
title: Biden's top economic adviser heads from White House to Harris campaign

description: From India's perspective, despite her many failings and an increasingly untenable position in domestic politics, Hasina acted as a source of regional stability by keeping religious extremists and anti-India forces under check.
title: Dhaka’s nasty turn: A lot to worry about for India
Hasina’s ouster puts a big question mark on India-Bangladesh defence ties

description: Amazon India launched its Great Freedom Festival from August 6th to August 11th, 2024, offering major discounts on products like smartphones, electronics, and home appliances. Featuring brands such as Apple, HP, and Xiaomi, customers using SBI Credit Cards received an additional 10% discount. Exclusive early access was available for Prime members starting from August 6th, 12 PM.
title: Amazon Great Freedom Festival sale: Check best deals on products
AAP not part of MVA, will go solo in Maharashtra

description: Hasina was in power for 15 consecutive years and maintained excellent relationships with both UPA and NDA governments. Hasina’s departure is a wild card moment for New Delhi, and one that it probably didn’t foresee in the near future. Things looked quite different in June when Harris was in India for PM Modi’s oath-taking ceremony. Her second visit in June, the first by a head of state after the BJP-led coalition came to power, showcased the usual bonhomie.
title: Hasina flees B'desh: Why experts call it 'worst-case scenario' for India
US presidential election: Harris narrows down VP pick choices to 2

description: Karisma Kapoor, a judge on India's Best Dancer Season 4, shared her experience and views on the show. She appreciated contestants' adaptability and reminisced about performing old songs. On reality shows' sob stories, she noted everyone's backstories but emphasized the show's focus on talent. She also mentioned enjoying sharing 90s anecdotes with the audience.
title: Karisma Kapoor reacts to sob stories being promoted on reality shows

description: Sakshi Malik, India's 2016 Rio Olympics bronze medalist and mentor to Nisha Dahiya, expressed support on X after Dahiya's emotional loss in the women’s freestyle 68 kg quarterfinal at the Paris Olympics. Malik praised Dahiya’s resilience, noting her disappointment over missing a medal rather than her injury. Despite leading 8-1, Dahiya suffered a dislocated finger and lost 10-8 to North Korea’s Sol Gum Pak. Dahiya still has a chance for a bronze if Pak reaches the final.
title: 'I just had a video call': Sakshi on Nisha's injury

description: The moment Indian fans have eagerly awaited will finally come tomorrow when the nation's golden boy Neeraj Chopra takes the field in the men's javelin throw qualification.
title: Paris Olympics Day 11: India's Full Schedule

description: The sudden departure of Sheikh Hasina as Prime Minister and her exit from Bangladesh has left India facing a multitude of uncertainties. For over 15 years, Hasina had been New Delhi's most steadfast partner, and during her tenure, the two nations experienced an unparalleled level of cooperation across various domains, including "cross-border trade and transit arrangements to security cooperation and people-to-people exchanges."
title: Five challenges Hasina’s departure poses for India

description: Bangladesh faced significant upheaval as Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina resigned and left the country after severe protests and a brutal crackdown that resulted in hundreds of deaths. General Waker-Uz-Zaman announced the military's takeover of the government, promising justice and urging calm. Hasina has reportedly fled to India, marking a dramatic end to her tenure. Hasina's son said that there will be no come back for her.
title: 'Mindless killing changed everything': How quota protests ended Sheikh Hasina's 15-yr reign
'After all her hard work, a minority ... ': Sheikh Hasina's son says she will not return to politics
AAP to contest all 36 Mumbai seats in upcoming Maharashtra elections

description: A mother from Wiltshire, England, named Lucy, 39, was left heartbroken when her six-year-old daughter's passport application was denied due to her name, Khaleesi, which was inspired by the hit TV show Game of Thrones. The UK Passport Office claimed that they couldn't issue a passport for Khaleesi without permission from Warner Brothers, the franchise owner, because of the name's trademark status.
title: Named after 'Game of Thrones' character, 6-yr-old UK girl denied passport

description: John Cena, after announcing his retirement from WWE, has expressed his deep admiration for Bollywood superstar Shah Rukh Khan. Cena revealed that SRK's Ted Talk motivated a significant change in his life. Recently, Cena met Khan at Anant Ambani's wedding, calling it an emotional and grateful encounter. Cena is also engaged in promoting his upcoming movie, Jackpot.
title: 'His words were beyond inspirational': John Cena praises Shah Rukh Khan
Watch: Bangladesh man loots Sheikh Hasina's sarees from her residence

description: Former Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina is set to leave for London after a brief stay in India, landing at Hindon Airbase in New Delhi. She met with Indian security officials including national security advisor Ajit Doval. Political unrest in Bangladesh led to her departure, with violent protests resulting in over 300 deaths and thousands arrested, prompting discussions of an interim government.
title: Former Bangladesh PM Sheikh Hasina to leave for London: Report
'Will support whatever decision Centre takes': Mamata on Bangladesh crisis
EAM Jaishankar briefs PM Modi as Bangladesh ex-PM Hasina's plane lands near Delhi

description: Dive in to stay updated on all the latest happenings in the world of glitz and glamour! From Rimi Sen on reports of plastic surgery to Shraddha Kapoor parting ways with Rahul Mody and Mumtaz on Rajesh Khanna's downfall, here's a look at what made headlines in the field of entertainment today!
title: Rimi Sen on reports of plastic surgery, Shraddha Kapoor part ways with Rahul Mody, Mumtaz on Rajesh Khanna's downfall: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: Roman Reigns' return at SummerSlam 2024 shattered records with nearly 100 million views on WWE social media, surpassing The Rock and CM Punk. Absent since his loss to Cody Rhodes at Wrestlemania 40, fans eagerly anticipated his comeback. Speculation now surrounds his next rival, with potential opponents including Cody Rhodes, Solo Sikoa, or Jacob Fatu.
title: Roman's SummerSlam return hit nearly 100 million views on WWE's social media
Who is Bangladesh army chief Waker-Uz-Zaman who announced Sheikh Hasina's resignation?

description: Olympic silver medalist Yusuf Dikec sparked a debate by asking Elon Musk if robots could win Olympic medals. Musk responded confidently, implying they could. Dikec, known for his relaxed approach to shooting, secured Turkey's first Olympic shooting medal alongside teammate Sevval Ilayda Tarhan. Musk's plans for humanoid robots, called Optimus, add intrigue to the discussion.
title: Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec asks Elon Musk ‘robot question’

description: Rahul Gandhi shared a video on Twitter on Monday showing him wearing shoes made by a cobbler he met earlier in Uttar Pradesh. The video shows Gandhi thanking the cobbler for the handmade shoes and appreciating his work.
title: 'Mera joota Hindustani': Rahul Gandhi gets handmade shoes from UP cobbler
'Honoured,' says Kangana on former Bangladesh PM Hasina coming to India

description: In the men's singles table tennis final at the Paris Olympics, Fan Zhendong defeated Sweden's Truls Moregardh 4-1 to win the gold medal. Despite losing, Moregardh captivated the audience with a remarkable 'snake' shot, a complex move that left Zhendong unable to respond, going viral on social media. This moment showcased Moregardh's skill and creativity, though he ultimately fell short against Zhendong's consistent performance, securing a silver medal after winning the first game.
title: Watch: Paddler's 'snake shot' at Olympics breaks internet

description: India's key defender Amit Rohidas missed the crucial Olympic men's hockey semifinal against Germany due to a one-match suspension upheld by the FIH. Rohidas received a red card for an accidental incident in the quarterfinal against Britain. Despite losing Rohidas, India managed a 1-1 draw and won the shootout to reach the semifinals.
title: 'Chak De India' star writes Rohidas' suspension letter

description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) has faced scrutiny over exam irregularities, including question paper leaks and grace marks. Despite claims it is a private entity, the NTA, incorporated under the Societies Registration Act, 1860, operates with government oversight and is subject to the RTI Act. It functions with a small team but outsources technical tasks to manage major exams efficiently.
title: NTA was incorporated under the Societies Registration Act: What it implies?

description: Samajwadi Party MP Jaya Bachchan raised objections in Rajya Sabha when chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar addressed her by her full name, linking it with her husband. She expressed discomfort over women’s identities being tied to their husbands. Chairman Dhankhar clarified the use of election certificate names and mentioned the provision to change them if needed.
title: 'New drama': Jaya Bachchan again objects to being called by husband's name in Rajya Sabha

description: NASA's Cygnus spacecraft faced an issue soon after launch, affecting its mission to the International Space Station. The glitch prevented initial burns to raise its orbit. Engineers from Northrop Grumman and NASA quickly intervened. The spacecraft carried crucial supplies and experiments for the ISS, including essential hardware and crew supplies.
title: Nasa’s Cygnus space suffers glitch after launch
Statue of Sheikh Hasina's father Sheikh Mujibur Rahman vandalised by protesters
Who is Bangladesh army chief who announced Sheikh Hasina's resignation?

description: Cryptocurrencies experienced a severe downturn on Monday as global markets faced heightened risk aversion. Bitcoin saw a dramatic fall of over 16%, while Ethereum also plummeted significantly.
title: Stock market crash: Ether sees steepest fall; 5 factors behind the crash
Watch: Sheikh Hasina takes military chopper to fly out of Dhaka

description: Former England cricketer and coach Graham Thorpe passed away at 55. Known for his remarkable career, he played 100 Test matches and 82 ODIs for England. Thorpe's passing prompted tributes from cricket legends like Ben Stokes, Michael Vaughan, Anil Kumble, and Shaun Udal. He was also a key figure in coaching, contributing to England's 2019 ODI World Cup win.
title: 'Gone far too young...': Graham Thorpe remembered by cricketers
Bangladesh unrest: Protestors storm PM Hasina's palace

description: Bangladesh PM Sheikh Hasina resigned amid violent quota protests, fleeing Dhaka with her sister for safety. Reports said 94 have died in fresh clashes, including 14 police officers. The government imposed a curfew, internet shutdown, and three-day holiday. India issued a travel advisory. The unrest, initially peaceful, targeted Hasina's governance and economic policies.
title: BSF issues 'high alert' along India-B'desh border: Top developments

description: The Delhi high court dismissed Arvind Kejriwal's plea challenging his arrest in the excise policy case, stating the arrest was justified. The court allowed Kejriwal to seek further relief from the trial court. Originally arrested by the ED in March, Kejriwal had secured bail in June, which was suspended.
title: Excise policy CBI case: Delhi HC dismisses Kejriwal's plea against arrest

description: Kangana Ranaut's lavish bungalow in Mumbai's Pali Hill area has been listed for sale for Rs 40 crore, confirmed by Simran Gupta of Code Estate. The property houses her production house, Manikarnika Films, and spans 3042 sq ft with an additional 500 sq ft parking.
title: Kangana Ranaut's Bandra bungalow up for sale at Rs 40cr

description: Former US President Donald Trump revealed his newfound friendship with Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg, who reportedly called multiple times. Zuckerberg apologized after Meta’s AI claimed a fictitious assassination attempt on Trump.
title: Donald Trump: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg called to apologise for the 'AI error'

description: Samajwadi Party chief Akhilesh Yadav criticized the BJP government, alleging their intent to undermine the rights of Muslims amid speculations of amending the Waqf Board Act. Yadav targeted UP Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath and urged those concerned with minorities to leave BJP, highlighting the proposed changes to the Waqf Act, which may limit the board's powers.
title: Akhilesh hits out at BJP for proposing to amend Waqf Act

description: CrowdStrike has refuted Delta Airlines' claim for damages related to the Microsoft outage on July 19. Delta's CEO Ed Bastian cited a $500 million loss and plans legal action. CrowdStrike, however, denied gross negligence and highlighted contractual liability limits, while stressing Delta's lack of response to offered assistance. The cybersecurity firm aims for a cooperative resolution.
title: Microsoft outage: CrowdStrike rejects Delta Airlines claims, sends this letter
SC refuses to stay Calcutta HC ruling on OBC status, seeks data from WB govt

description: A BJP delegation met the family of a 12-year-old rape survivor in Ayodhya and urged the Uttar Pradesh government to increase the compensation from Rs 5 lakh to Rs 25 lakh. The prime accused, affiliated with the Samajwadi Party, has been involved in similar crimes before. The delegation assured that strict action would be taken.
title: Ayodhya rape case: 'Accused SP leader had committed similar crimes earlier'
Akhilesh accuses BJP of politicising Ayodhya rape case for electoral gain

description: The National Payments Corporation of India implemented new FASTag regulations effective August 1, 2024, aimed at improving toll collection efficiency. Users need to update KYC details for FASTags issued between three to five years ago by October 31, 2024, and replace FASTags older than five years. The regulations also include linking vehicle information and uploading photos for proper identification.
title: New FASTag rules explained: Complete these procedures by Oct 31 to avoid inconvenience

description: Prashant Kishor announced that on October 2, a new political party would be formed by the citizens of Bihar. This initiative aims to break away from the 30-year governance of Lalu Prasad Yadav, Nitish Kumar, and the BJP. Kishor clarified his role will remain unchanged within this newly formed political party, created by one crore people of Bihar.
title: On October 2, 1 crore people will float new political party in Bihar, says Prashant Kishor

description: The Paris Olympics boxing event saw a gender row involving Algeria's Imane Khelif and Taiwan's Lin Yu-ting, both backed by the IOC. IOC president Thomas Bach supported the athletes, challenging the IBA's flawed gender tests. The controversy intensified after Bulgarian boxer Svetlana Kamenova Staneva protested her loss to Lin using an 'X' sign, highlighting chromosome differences.
title: Why 'gender row' in Paris Olympics boxing refuses to die down

description: A five thousandths of a second separated USA's gold medallist Lyles and Kishane Thompson of Jamaica as both clocked 9.79 seconds in the first such wind-legal 100m race in history that saw all eight runners finishing under 10 seconds. The bronze medal went to Lyles's American teammate Fred Kerly.
title: Noah Lyles: Olympic gold despite asthma, dyslexia, depression

description: Former minority affairs minister Mukhtar Abbas Naqvi emphasized the need for reforms in the Waqf system, advocating for greater accountability and transparency. The government planned to introduce a Bill to amend the 1995 law, mandating property registration and inclusion of women in Waqf boards. Opposition came from several Muslim organizations and leaders, including Asaduddin Owaisi.
title: 'Waqf system must come out of touch me not syndrome'

description: Manu Bhaker, the talented Indian shooter, will be the flag bearer for her country at the Olympic closing ceremony on Sunday. Her remarkable performance at the Paris Games has etched her name in the annals of Indian sports history. In the individual 10m air pistol event, Bhaker displayed exceptional skill and composure, ultimately securing a bronze medal.
title: Manu Bhaker to be India's flag bearer at closing ceremony
'Death chambers, playing with lives': SC on coaching centre tragedy in Delhi

description: On the fifth anniversary of the abrogation of Article 370, PDP president Mehbooba Mufti and other leaders, including those from Apni Party and National Conference, were allegedly placed under house arrest. They criticized the constitutional and ethical implications of the abrogation and lamented the lack of an elected Assembly in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: Mehbooba Mufti alleges house arrest on Article 370 abrogation anniversary

description: India's assistant coach Abhishek Nayar attributed the loss to Sri Lanka in the second ODI to spin-friendly conditions, highlighting the Indian team's challenges against spin bowling. Jeffrey Vandersay's six-wicket haul handed India a 32-run loss as they struggled to chase 241, ending at 208 all out. The Indian middle order failed to build partnerships, contributing to the defeat.

description: Paris Olympics witnessed the closest ever men's 100m final in modern history and two statistics highlight that the most. One, the difference between the gold and the silver medal was five thousandth of a second. And two, it marked the first ever men's 100m race where each of the eight runners clocked under 10 seconds with a legal wind factor.
title: Explained: How 5000th of a second decided Lyles's 100m gold

description: A woman in Bengaluru was sexually assaulted during her morning walk on Friday. Despite bravely resisting and managing to break free, she had to fend off an assailant who tried to kiss her. Unfortunately, no one came to her aid despite her screams. The incident was captured on local CCTV footage.

description: In the second ODI between India and Sri Lanka, Sri Lanka won by 32 runs, taking a 1-0 lead in the series. A key moment was Shreyas Iyer's direct hit run out of Kamindu Mendis in the last over. India, despite restricting Sri Lanka to 240/9, faltered against spin and were bundled out for 208 in 42.2 overs.

The suspects were arrested in West Bengal in April following a bomb blast on March 1, injuring 10 people. The NIA conducted extensive searches across multiple locations during the investigation.
title: Rameshwaram cafe blast: NIA takes 2 terrorists to Bengaluru eatery for spot inspection

description: During the ECS Bulgaria T10 match, Afyonkarahisar SHS's Kursad Dalyan made a remarkable catch against VTU-MU Pleven. Dalyan's unconventional effort helped restrict Pleven to 40/8, contributing to his team's victory. The catch occurred when Anandhu Krishna attempted a drive, only for Dalyan to complete the catch using his shoe.
title: 'Leg Before Catch': An unconventional catch goes viral - Watch

description: Eight unidentified landslide victims were buried at Puthumala with multi-faith prayers. The disaster had previously destroyed two villages and led to 381 deaths. Rescue and search operations continued with new technologies deployed. Concrete poles marked the graves, and DNA samples collected for identification. Police increased security due to theft reports and volunteers continued food distribution amidst controversies.
title: Kerala mourns as 8 victims laid to rest, only a number marking their graves

description: West Bengal Governor CV Ananda Bose shared his views on his relationship with Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee, noting a distinction between her roles as an individual, a professional, and a politician. Addressing disputes, Bose claimed no pending government bills in his office and called for a White Paper on state finances, highlighting concerns over financial management.

description: Mumtaz talks about Rajesh Khanna's downfall and says that there were producers and directors who did his 'chamchagiri' which led to his downfall. There would be parties at his house and his girlfriend Anju Mahendru would play host till 3 am!
title: Mumtaz recalls Rajesh Khanna had 'chamchas' who led to his downfall
‘Such a consequential president’: Nancy Pelosi says US should add Joe Biden to Mount Rushmore

description: The US anticipated an imminent attack by Iran and Hezbollah on Israel and alerted its G7 allies. Secretary of State Antony Blinken sought last-minute diplomatic efforts to prevent conflict. Israel's Prime Minister Netanyahu considered a preemptive strike if clear evidence of an attack was found, following recent high-level assassinations in Beirut and Tehran, blamed on Israel.
title: Iran could attack Israel within next 24 to 48 hours: Report
MUDA imbroglio: Congress throws weight behind Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah

description: India and Sri Lanka's three-match ODI series has been marred by controversy following a Decision Review System incident in the second ODI. The incident arose from a call involving Virat Kohli. Sri Lanka's spinner Jeffrey Vandersay's impressive performance, taking 6 for 33, helped bowl India out for 208 in 42.2 overs. However, the DRS decision left the Sri Lankan team frustrated.

Army opens fire after detecting suspicious movement along LoC, search operations under way

Premadasa Stadium in Colombo.

description: A BJP delegation visited the gang rape survivor's family in Ayodhya to provide security and support. The mother reported ongoing threats and demanded the death penalty for the accused. Minister Narendra Kashyap condemned the Samajwadi Party's demands for DNA tests, while CM Yogi Adityanath took significant action against the accused's illegal assets.

description: The tech industry witnessed significant layoffs in July 2024, with over 8,000 professionals losing their jobs across 34 companies. Major layoffs include Intel's 15,000 job cuts and UKG's 2,200. Other notable companies like Microsoft, Intuit, and Dyson also downsized. Startups and smaller firms such as ReshaMandi, Koo, and WayCool faced severe cuts and closures.

description: The Tokyo Olympics bronze medallists will have only 15 players available to play the last-four clash instead of a full squad of 16 after defender Amit Rohidas was suspended for one match following his red card in the quarterfinal against Great Britain. India will play their semifinal for August 6, eyeing their first Olympic hockey final in 44 years.

description: Television actress Sana Makbul won Bigg Boss OTT season 3 and celebrated her victory with her rumoured boyfriend, Srikanth Bureddy. She confirmed their wedding plans, stating it will happen gradually. Srikanth expressed pride in her dignified gameplay. Sana mentioned she stood firm on her beliefs despite facing criticism. She won a cash prize of Rs 25 lakh.
